(% class=&amp;#34;StyleStyleBold12pt&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size:13.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)Buzas 12(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt&amp;#34; %) Race and International Politics: How Racial Prejudice Can Shape Discord and Cooperation among Great Powers DISSERTATION Presented in Partial Fulfillment of the Requirements for the Degree Doctor of Philosophy in the Graduate School of The Ohio State University By Zoltán I. Búzás, M.A. Graduate Program in Political Science The Ohio State University 2012(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 8pt; background: lime; mso-highlight: lime&amp;#34; %)


(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)I build on Ted Hopf’s social cognitive conception of identity where identities function as lenses of perception. 189 Identities are social, because they are the result of interactions with the social environment. At the most general level, identity refers to actors’ self-understanding acquired through social interactions. Identities are also cognitive heuristics which allow us, cognitive misers, to cope with the complexity of the world. They function as lenses of perception, or what Hopf calls “axis of interpretation” 187 Gause III 2003, 273. 188 Hopf 1998, 187. 189 Hopf 2002.57 and Linda Alcoff calls “interpretive horizons.” 190 They make “threats and opportunities, enemies and allies, intelligible, thinkable, and possible.” 191 Identities as lenses of perception do more than just tell us who we are. They also tell us who others are. Identities are “mutually constructed and evolving images of self and other.” 192 The insight that identities function as lenses of perception has provided a fruitful starting point for several different theories. John Owen built his explanation of democratic peace on the assumption that “people perceive their material environment through ‘lenses’, formed by the ideas they hold, that give that environment meaning.” 193 Richard Herrmann and Michael Fischerkeller provided an image theory of foreign policy where behavior is largely a function of actors’ strategic images of others. Based on judgments about relative power, culture, and threat or opportunity, the authors identify multiple images and strategic behaviors associated with them. 194 Although Herrmann and Fischerkeller briefly touch on race, they limit its relevance primarily to the asymmetrical power relations of the “colony” image. They assume that race is irrelevant in more symmetrical power relations such as that of the “enemy” image. As discussed in Chapter 1, the dissertation extends the relevance of race to the symmetrical relations of great power politics, including the “enemy” image. My contribution lies in applying the insight that identities function as lenses of threat perception to racial identities. Racial identities, like any identity, vary along two 190 Alcoff 2006; Hopf 2002,.5. 191 Cronin 1999,18; Hopf 2002, 16. 192 Jepperson, Wendt, and Katzenstein 1996, 59. 193 Owen 1997, 18. 194 Herrmann and Fischerkeller 1995. 58 main dimensions: content and contestation. 195 Since, as explained in the introductory chapter, I use race as a cause rather than as an effect, I bracket contestation and focus on content. (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime; mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)Racial identity shapes threat perception through the prejudices it contains.(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %) The visibility of racial identity facilitates the development of prejudices. (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)Based on(%%) our limited (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)experiences we form categories of others, attach various attributes to them, and then over-generalize these attributes to all members of the category(%%).(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) 196 Prejudices are primarily the consequence of our being cognitive misers, but they may also be reinforced by other needs and interests. They may satisfy humans’ need for positive self-esteem and may contribute in subtle but powerful ways to the maintenance of existing power relations. 197 Although their strength varies across levels of education, geographic location, age, gender, or level of income, prejudices are surprisingly widespread and resilient. One concern in the race literature regarding racial theorizing that relies on prejudices is that it reduces racism to individual idiosyncrasy and misses its broader structural aspects. 198 Indeed, a significant portion of the prejudice literature tends to embrace methodological and ontological individualism. Theodor Adorno’s classic study located prejudice in the “authoritarian personality,” and more recent cognitive-behavioral approaches locate it in the individual mind. 199 Nonetheless, there is no good reason to assume that prejudices are necessarily individual, rather than structural. The assumption 195 Abdelal et al. 2009. 196 Allport 1958 1954,147. 197 Maykovich 1971, 448; Mercer 1995. 198 Bourne 2001; Silliman 2003; Wight 2003. 199 Adorno 1950; Corlett 2003; Levine and Pataki 2004.59 that prejudices are individualist has recently come under attack in social psychology. 200 As mentioned earlier, social identity theory revealed the social origins of prejudices. In the same vein, I conceive of prejudices embedded in racial identities as the microstructures which help uphold larger material, institutional and legal macro-structures. They are embedded in the larger social structure, are relational, and are transmitted socially, which makes them as social as they are cognitive. By embedding them in racial identities, I hope to avoid the reductionist trap associated with theories of racial prejudices. Prejudices help racial identity shape threat perception in two ways. (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %)First, racial prejudices facilitate the activation of racial identities by providing the cognitive associations on which activation depends.(% style=&amp;#34;background:lime; mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %) Because agents have multiple identities, the activation of racial identities is necessary in order to perceive others through a racial lens. Activation (%%)is a cognitive process which can occur automatically, but(% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %) can (%%)also (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)be facilitated by a wide range of cues provided by the media and politicians. It depends on the prior existence of conscious or unconscious cognitive associations between racial others and particular characteristics, events, or policies(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %). Such close associations usually take the form of prejudices. The literature on racial cues and on playing the “race card” provides strong evidence in this regard. 201 For example, the close connection in the American mind between crime and African Americans can activate racial perception if one is exposed to images or statements about crime, even if no direct reference to race is 200 Dixon and Levine 2012, 6-10. 201 Gilens 1996; Mendelberg 2001; White, 2007. 60 made. 202 This implicit activation is the more powerful because it can circumvent norms prohibiting racism by avoiding explicit reference to race. Similar activation of racial identities as a lens of perception can occur towards racial groups inhabiting other states if one is exposed to images or statements which focus on characteristics closely associated with that racial group. Although much of this literature in American politics emphasizes the instrumental role of manipulative elites and the media in activating racial prejudices, there is nothing in the logic of activation that requires instrumentalism. In practice (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)it is often the manipulative elite and the media that provide racial cues,(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) but sometimes they provide racial cues automatically, without being motivated by some self-interest.

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %) 

==== Guarantees eventual conflict ====

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; %)
(% class=&amp;#34;StyleStyleBold12pt&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size:13.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)Buzas 12(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt&amp;#34; %) Race and International Politics: How Racial Prejudice Can Shape Discord and Cooperation among Great Powers DISSERTATION Presented in Partial Fulfillment of the Requirements for the Degree Doctor of Philosophy in the Graduate School of The Ohio State University By Zoltán I. Búzás, M.A. Graduate Program in Political Science The Ohio State University 2012(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 8pt; background: lime; mso-highlight: lime&amp;#34; %)


(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph&amp;#34; %)
 

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph&amp;#34; %)
(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)Race is underappreciated in mainstream IR theory(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %). (% style=&amp;#34;background: lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)Realist approaches pay attention to ethnicity and nationalism, but not to (%%)race and (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime; mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)racism(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %). Stephen Van Evera provides a systematic discussion of nationalism and war, while Barry Posen deploys the security dilemma to explain ethnic conflict. 58 Even John Mearsheimer makes a quick reference to “hypernationalism” as a factor which (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %)may shape patterns of conflict. 59 Democratic peace theory largely neglects race. (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)According to liberalism race should not matter, but there are reasons to think that it does(%%). A look at the list of (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)imperialist conflicts(%%) and covert operations (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)performed by white liberal democracies against non-white nondemocracies leaves one wondering whether race is indeed epiphenomenal(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;background:lime;mso-highlight: lime&amp;#34; %).(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) 60 While dyadic versions of democratic peace emphasize that democracies are peaceful only when dealing with other democracies, according to monadic versions liberal democracies 58 Posen 1993; Van Evera 1994. 59 Mearsheimer 1990. It is worth noting that Mearsheimer sees hypernationalism as the result of intense European security competition and so not independent of structural forces. 60 One study identifies thirty-three imperial wars involving white liberal democracies against non-white political entities between 1838 and 1920, and eight American covert operations in non-white countries during the Cold War. For further details see Rosato 2003, 589-590.17 should be peaceful regardless of the regime type of their counterparts. Yet Dan Reiter and Allan Stam note that “(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)What makes imperial wars especially disturbing to the liberal conscience is that they demonstrate also that it is easier to generate public consent if the target is racially or ethnically different from the attacker(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %).” 61 English School approaches incorporate nationalism as a fundamental institution of international society but reserve a less central role for race, despite its attention to the “standard of ‘civilization’” in international politics. 62 Race has always lurked in the background of international society, but only more recently started to receive some attention. 63 Constructivist approaches provide exciting accounts of how gender, religion, culture, or national identity matters in international politics. 64 Yet race regrettably receives less attention. A recent series of edited volumes on civilization in world politics constitutes an important exception. 6

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; %)
 

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;text-indent:.5in&amp;#34; %)
 </headline></objectSummary><objectSummary><link rel="http://www.xwiki.org/rel/object" href="http://opencaselist.paperlessdebate.com/xwiki/rest/wikis/opencaselist/spaces/Texas-San%20Antonio/pages/nerison-stroud%20Aff/objects/Admin.EntryClass/5"/><link rel="http://www.xwiki.org/rel/properties" href="http://opencaselist.paperlessdebate.com/xwiki/rest/wikis/opencaselist/spaces/Texas-San%20Antonio/pages/nerison-stroud%20Aff/objects/Admin.EntryClass/5/properties"/><id>opencaselist:Texas-San Antonio.nerison-stroud Aff:5dd73ee5-6756-4a60-b1ee-474344e217a8</id><guid>5dd73ee5-6756-4a60-b1ee-474344e217a8</guid><pageId>opencaselist:Texas-San Antonio.nerison-stroud Aff</pageId><wiki>opencaselist</wiki><space>Texas-San Antonio</space><pageName>nerison-stroud Aff</pageName><className>Admin.EntryClass</className><number>5</number><headline>==== Nuclear reactors are designed to create and controlled nuclear reaction. A critical mass of Uranium 235 is bombarded with neutrons. These neutrons cause the Uranium to decay into krypton and barium, plus kinetic energy and a few spare neutrons. Those neutrons strike other uranium atoms, which decay and given off more neutrons striking more uranium atoms. This is the exact process of a fission bomb, in a cascading chain reaction that accelerates to release catastrophic energy. But in a reactor this is slowed down. We use a neutralizing medium to retard the speed of neutrons to prevent this catastrophic acceleration. ====

==== This sustained detonation heats water to super-heated levels, converting it into steam with a huge amount of force. We then drive the steam through a turbine, forcing it to spin and driving magnets past alternating magnets of opposite polarity. These magnets are where the electricity is produced. Our usable energy comes not from the nuclear reaction or the heat, not from detonation or radioactive decay or even steam, but by creating this resistance between alternative poles. So as the positive swings past negative, negative swings past positive, in an never-ending waltz of opposites, the means are produced for us to turn on our lights and charge our laptops. ====

==== Since 1945, when the US saw the awe-inspiring power of the nuclear bomb, we&amp;#39;ve been pursuing nuclear energy. Today the US has 104 nuclear reactors producing 807 billion kilo-Watt hours of power – 30% of global production.  The threat of that explosion still haunts our nuclear dreams, so restrictions proliferate. From the careful vetting of all reactors by the Department of Energy and Nuclear Regulatory Commission, to the careful control of the rate at which plants can produce energy, to the literally thousands of safety measures imposed, our society has become the nuclear reactor, slowly exploding while the government does everything in its power to slow the release of neutrons, to manage the chain reaction. The nuclear reactor typifies the model upon which these politics have been based. ====

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %) 

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; %)
(% class=&amp;#34;StyleStyleBold12pt&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size:13.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)Baudrillard 85 (% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 8.0pt&amp;#34; %)Jean Baudrillard.  Simulacra and Simulation.  1985.  Page 32-34.

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph&amp;#34; %)
(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)The apotheosis of simulation: the nuclear(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %). However, the balance of terror is never anything but the spectacular slope of a system of deterrence that has insinuated itself from the inside into all the cracks of daily life. (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)Nuclear suspension(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %) only (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)serves(%%) to seal (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)the trivialized system of deterrence that is at the heart of the media, of the violence without consequences that reigns throughout the world(%%), of the aleatory apparatus of all the choices that are made for us. (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime; mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)The most insignificant of our behaviors is regulated by neutralized(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %), indifferent, equivalent signs, by zero-sum (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)signs(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) like those that regulate the &amp;#34;strategy of games&amp;#34; (but the true equation is elsewhere, (% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 8pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: lime; mso-highlight: lime&amp;#34; %)and the unknown is (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)precisely (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)that variable of simulation(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %) (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)which makes(%%) of (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)the atomic(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) arsenal itself (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)a(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;background:lime;mso-highlight: lime&amp;#34; %) (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)hyperreal form, a (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime; mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)simulacrum that dominates everything and reduces all(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) &amp;#34;ground-level&amp;#34; (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)events to(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) being nothing but (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime; mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)ephemeral scenarios, transforming (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %)the (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)life (%%)left us (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)into survival(%%), into a stake without stakes - (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)not even into a life insurance policy: into a policy that already has no value)(%%). (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)It is not the (%%)direct (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)threat of atomic destruction that paralyzes our lives, it is deterrence that gives them leukemia. And this deterrence comes from that fact that even the real atomic clash is precluded(%%) -(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) precluded like the eventuality of the real in a system of signs. The whole world pretends to believe in the reality of this threat (this is understandable on the part of the military, the gravity of their exercise and the discourse of their &amp;#34;strategy&amp;#34; are at stake), but it is precisely at this level that there are no strategic stakes. The whole originality of the situation lies in the improbability of destruction. Deterrence precludes war - the archaic violence of expanding systems. Deterrence itself is the neutral, implosive violence of metastable systems or systems in involution. There is no longer a subject of deterrence, nor an adversary nor a strategy - it is a planetary structure of the annihilation of stakes. Atomic war, like the Trojan War, will not take place. The risk of (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)nuclear annihilation only serves as a pretext,(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) through the sophistication of weapons (a sophistication that surpasses any possible objective to such an extent that it is itself a symptom of nullity), (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)for installing a universal security system,(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) a universal lockup and control system (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)whose deterrent effect is(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %) not at all (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight: lime&amp;#34; %)aimed at(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %) (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)an atomic clash (which was never in question, except without a doubt in the very initial stages of the cold war, when one still confused the nuclear apparatus with conventional war) but, rather, at the much greater probability of (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)any real event, of anything that would be an event in the general system and upset its balance(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %). The balance of terror is the terror of balance. Deterrence is not a strategy, it circulates and is exchanged between nuclear protagonists exactly as is international capital in the orbital zone of monetary speculation whose fluctuations suffice to control all global exchanges. Thus the money of destruction (without any reference to real destruction, any more than floating capital has a real referent of production) that circulates in nuclear orbit suffices to control all the violence and potential conflicts around the world. (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)What is hatched(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) in the shadow of this mechanism with the pretext of a maximal, &amp;#34;objective,&amp;#34; threat, and thanks to Damocles&amp;#39; nuclear sword, (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)is the(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) perfection of the (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background: lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)best system of control that has ever existed.(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) And the progressive satellization of the whole planet through this hypermodel of security. (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)The same goes for peaceful nuclear power stations. Pacification does not distinguish between the civil and the military: everywhere where irreversible apparatuses of control are elaborated,(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) everywhere where the notion of security becomes omnipotent, everywhere where the norm replaces the old arsenal of laws and violence (including war), it is (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)the system of deterrence (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %)that (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)grows, and around it grows the historical, social, and political desert(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %).(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) A gigantic involution that makes every conflict, every finality, every confrontation contract in proportion to this blackmail that interrupts, neutralizes, freezes them all. (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)No longer can any revolt, any story be deployed according to its own logic because it risks annihilation. No strategy is possible any longer(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %), and escalation is only a puerile game given over to the military. (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)The political stake is dead,(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;background:lime;mso-highlight: lime&amp;#34; %) (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)only simulacra of conflicts and carefully circumscribed stakes remain. The &amp;#34;space race&amp;#34; played exactly the same role as nuclear escalation. This is why the space program was so easily able to replace it in the 1960s (Kennedy/Khrushchev), or to develop concurrently as a form of &amp;#34;peaceful coexistence.&amp;#34; Because what, ultimately, is the function of the space program, of the conquest of the moon, of the launching of satellites if not the institution of a model of universal gravitation, of satellization of which the lunar module is the perfect embryo? (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)Programmed microcosm, where nothing can be left to chance. Trajectory,(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %) (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)energy, calculation, physiology, psychology, environment - nothing can be left to contingencies, this is the total universe of the norm - the Law no longer exists, it is the operational immanence of every detail that is law. A universe purged of all threat of meaning,(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) in a state of asepsis and weightlessness - it is this very perfection that is fascinating. The exaltation of the crowds was not a response to the event of landing on the moon or of sending a man into space (this would be, rather, the fulfillment of an earlier dream), rather, we are dumbfounded by the perfection of the programming and the technical manipulation, by the immanent wonder of the programmed unfolding of events. Fascination with the maximal norm and the mastery of probability. Vertigo of the model, which unites with the model of death, but without fear or drive. Because if the law, with its aura of transgression, if order, with its aura of violence, still taps a perverse imaginary, the norm fixes, fascinates, stupefies, and makes every imaginary involute. One no longer fantasizes about the minutiae of a program. Just watching it produces vertigo. The vertigo of a world without flaws. Now, it is the same model of programmatic infallibility, of maximum security and deterrence that today controls the spread of the social. (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime; mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)There lies the true nuclear fallout: the meticulous operation of technology serves as a model for the meticulous operation of the social. (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %)Here as well,(% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %) nothing will be left to chance(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %), moreover this is the essence of socialization, which began centuries ago, but which has now entered its accelerated phase, toward a limit that one believed would be explosive (revolution), but which for the moment is translated by an inverse, implosive, irreversible process: (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)the generalized deterrence of chance, of accident, of transversality, of finality, of contradiction, rupture, or complexity in a sociality(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %) illuminated by the norm, (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)doomed to the descriptive transparency of mechanisms of information(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %). In fact, the spatial and nuclear models do not have their own ends: neither the discovery of the moon, nor military and strategic superiority. Their truth is to be the models of simulation, the model vectors of a system of planetary control (where even the superpowers of this scenario are not free - the whole world is satellized).

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) 

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph&amp;#34; %)
**Caught up in this universe purged of meaning, of chance, of any eventuality, caught up in society like those neutrons striving to interact and explode but prevented by this banalizing medium of restrictions, we find that we are still not as safe as we&amp;#39;d hope.**



(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph&amp;#34; %)
**~ **



(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph&amp;#34; %)
**The reactors only produce through the programmed resistance. The turbines spin from negative to positive to negative and an effect is produced: The US marches onwards! So we create catastrophe, we create resistance, we create the illusion of meaning so that the workers will continue to toil on. This is the history of the nuclear, demonstrated in our ever-accelerating race with the USSR. We&amp;#39;ve now spun past the USSR, yet the film strip continues to play, projecting spectacles of nuclear catastrophe upon our collective psyches. We&amp;#39;ll suffice to focus on one: the Three Mile Island meltdown. In 1979 a water-pump broke down in the Three Mile Island nuclear power plant. Of course, the plant had monitoring systems, fail-safe systems, and redundant controls to deal with such a problem. But those monitoring systems were malfunctioning, and when the staff dumped the excess water from the pump system, they exacerbated the problem. The pump was broken, but they were suffering from a lack of water, not an excess, and when they dumped the water they began a meltdown which flooded the containment building with radiation and threatened to poison all of Pennsylvania. The Nuclear Regulatory Commission came and falsely certified that disaster was averted, that all was safe. One can see the workings of deterrence here – the monomaniacal focus on one problem that in fact exacerbated the problem, or the insistence by the NRC that crisis was averted.         More interesting however, is the working of turbine-resistance. Just 12 days before the Three Mile Island accident saw the release of the blockbuster movie The China Syndrome. Jane Fonda ventured to a nuclear power plant in Pennsylvania to film a news story on nuclear safety. But the plant acts up to give a show to the cameras. Like in Three Mile Island, a water-pump malfunctions. Like in Three Mile Island, the operators thought there was too much pressure and dumped the water. Like in Three Mile Island, they were suffering from a lack of water, not an excess. Like in Three Mile Island, a Pennsylvanian plant was threatening all of Pennsylvania.  Baudrillard explains that: “The China Syndrome … is not a stranger to the &amp;#34;real&amp;#34; accident in Three Mile Island, … the real corresponded point by point to the simulacrum, including the suspended, incomplete character of the catastrophe, which is essential from the point of view of deterrence: the real arranged itself … to produce a simulation of catastrophe.”  Trapped within the turbine of politics, we must constantly produce simulated catastrophes, we must produces threats and resistance to drive politics onwards. Just view all the false, exaggerated emergencies, and the blind readiness to believe in them. Without resistance our fuel burns and burns, but nothing happens. With resistance, citizens voraciously fight for Liberal or Conservative, Democratic or Republican, spinning around and around in a protest which does nothing but elevate the government even more.**



(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph&amp;#34; %)
**~ **



(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph&amp;#34; %)
**So, we find ourselves sitting along the slope of a huge energy system, accelerating exponentially in a nuclear chain reaction. This slope either leads to the chill or deterrence or the infinite growth of energy. Either way our delayed atomic bombs will explode, either way there will be catastrophe – the only question is whether that catastrophe will be positive or negative. Will we produce continual Three Mile Islands, paralyzed by deterrence, or will we move forward to a new and unpredictable energy future?**



(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; %)
**~ **



(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; %)
(% class=&amp;#34;StyleStyleBold12pt&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size:13.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)**Baudrillard 2002** (% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 8.0pt&amp;#34; %)Jean Baudrillard. “The Fate of Energy.” The Transparency of Evil: Essays on Extreme Phenomena. Trans. James Benedict. New York: Verso Books (2002). 100-105.

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; %)
 

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)AII the events described here are susceptible to two kinds of diagnosis: physical and metaphysical. From the physical point of view, (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)we are(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %) apparently (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)dealing with a(%%) sort of (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)massive phase transition in a human system in disequilibrium(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %).(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) As with physical systems proper, this phase transition remains largely mysterious for us, (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)but the catastrophic development(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %) in question (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime; mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)is in itself neither beneficial nor malignant: it is simply catastrophic(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt; background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %),(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) in the literal sense of the word. The prototype of this chaotic declination, of this hypersensitivity to initial conditions, is the fate of energy. (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)Our(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;background:lime;mso-highlight: lime&amp;#34; %) (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime; mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)culture has seen the development of the liberation of energy as an(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt; background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %) (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)irreversible process(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %). All previous cultures have depended on a reversible pact with the world, on a stable ordering of things in which energy release certainly played a role, but never on the liberation of energy as a basic principle. For us, (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)energy is the first thing to be &amp;#39;liberated&amp;#39;(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %), and all subsequent forms of liberation are founded on this model. (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)Man himself is liberated as an energy source, so becoming the motor of a history and of a speeding-up of that history.(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %) (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime; mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)Energy is a(%%) sort of (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime; mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)fantasy projection which nourishes all modernity&amp;#39;s(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) industrial and technical (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)dreams(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %); energy is also what tends to give our conception of man the sense of a dynamics of the will. We know, (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)however(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %), thanks to the most recent findings of modern physics on the phenomena of turbulence, chaos and catastrophe, that any flow - indeed, (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)any linear process - when it is speeded up is inflected in a curious way, a way that produces catastrophe. The catastrophe that lies in wait for us is not connected to a depletion of resources. Energy itself, in all its forms, will become more and more abundant(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) (at any rate, within the broadest time frame that could conceivably concern us as humans). (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)Nuclear energy is inexhaustible,(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt&amp;#34; %) as are solar energy, the force of the tides, of the great fluxes of nature, and indeed of natural catastrophes, earthquakes and volcanoes (and technological imagination may be relied on to find ways and means to harness them). (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime; mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)What is alarming(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %), by contrast, (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)is the dynamics of disequilibrium, the uncontrollability of the energy system itself, which is capable of getting out of hand in deadly fashion in very short order.(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) We have already had a few spectacular demonstrations of the consequences of the liberation of nuclear energy (Hiroshima, Chernobyl), but it must be remembered that (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)any chain reaction(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %) at all, (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)viral or radioactive, has catastrophic potential.(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) Our degree of protection from pandemics is epitomized by the utterly useless glacis that often surrounds nuclear power stations. It is not impossible that the whole system of world-transformation through energy has already entered a virulent and epidemic stage corresponding to (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)the most essential character of energy (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %)itself: a fall, (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)a differential, an imbalance – a catastrophe in miniature which to begin with has positive effects but which, once overtaken by its own impetus, assumes the dimensions of a global catastrophe.(%%) (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime; mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)Energy may be looked upon as a cause which produces effects, but it is also an effect which is self-reproducing(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %), and can thus cease to obey any law of causality. The paradox of energy is that it implies a revolution on the level of causes and a revolution on the level of effects – each, practically speaking, independent of the other. (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)It thus becomes the locus(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %) (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)not only of a chain of causes but also(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 8pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: lime; mso-highlight: lime&amp;#34; %) (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)of an unhindered flood of effects.(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %) (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight: lime&amp;#34; %)Energy (%%)thus (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)enters a state of superfusion. The whole system of world-transformation enters a state of superfusion. (%%)Formerly a material and productive variable, (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)energy has now become a vertiginous process feeding upon itsel(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)f(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) (which is, incidentally, why there is no danger that we shall run out of it). Consider New York City. It is a miracle that everything starts afresh each morning, considering how much energy has been used up the day before. The phenomenon is indeed inexplicable until one realizes that no rational principle of energy loss is at work here, and that the functioning of a megalopolis such as New York contradicts the second law of thermodynamics: the city feeds on its own hubbub, its own waste, its own carbon-dioxide emissions – energy arising from the expenditure of energy, thanks to a sort of miracle of substitution. Experts who base their calculations solely on the quantitative aspects of an energy system inevitably underestimate the peculiar energy source contributed by energy discharge itself. In the case of New York this discharge is completely spectacularized – supercharged by its own image. (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)In The Supermale(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %), Alfred Jarry describes a superfused energy of this order in connection with sexual activity, but it may also occur in the cases of mental and mechanical energy: (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)as Jarry&amp;#39;s quintuplet crosses Siberia(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) in the wake of the Trans-Siberian, (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)some velocipedists die, yet carry on cycling. Rigor mortis is replaced by mobilitas mortis, and the dead(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %) (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)rider pedals on indefinitely, even accelerating, as a function of inertia. The energy released is boosted by the inertia of the dead.(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %) Here (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)we are reminded of Mandeville&amp;#39;s Fable of the Bees, according to which the splendor of a society derives from its vices, its ills, its excesses(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %), and its shortcomings. This thesis is diametrically opposed to the economists&amp;#39; claim that if something is expended, it must obviously be produced. On the contrary, the more we spend, the more energy and wealth increase. The energy in question is, precisely, that of catastrophe - an energy that economic calculations can never take into account. A particular kind of exaltation familiar in mental processes is now to be encountered in material processes as well. All these considerations are quite unintelligible in terms of equivalence: they can be understood only in the context of reversibility and inordinacy. (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)Thus the energy of New Yorkers flows from their fouled air, from their speeded-up pace of life(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %), from the panic and asphyxia created by their unimaginably inhuman environment. It is even quite probable that drugs, and all the compulsive activities that drugs bring in their train, also contribute to the level of vitality and crudely metabolic vigor of the city. (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime; mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)Everything plays a part - from the most refined activities to the most degraded: a total chain reaction(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %).(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) Any notion of normal functioning has evaporated. (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)All beings conspire(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) (as one might have said in the eighteenth century) (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)in the same excess, the same dramatic over excitement, which, leaving the need to live far behind, has much more to do with an unreal obsession with survival - with that glacial passion for survival which seizes hold of everyone and feeds off its own ferocity(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %).(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)To try to wean New Yorkers(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %) away (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight: lime&amp;#34; %)from their (%%)extravagance and (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime; mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)wastefulness, or to get them to slow the inhuman rhythm at which they live, would be mistaken(%%) on two counts. In the first place, (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)they do not find their activity exhausting(%%), though it would be for normal people: on the contrary, (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)they draw an abnormal energy from it.(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) Secondly, it would be humiliating for them if they were obliged to slow down and economize on their energy flow; this would represent a lowering of their collective status and compromise their claim to an immoderation and urban mobility which are without equal in the world and of which they all partake, whether consciously or unconsciously. (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)The dangers threatening the human species are thus less risks of default (exhaustion of natural resources, dilapidation of the environment, etc.) than risks of excess: runaway energy flows, chain reactions, or frenzied autonomous developments(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %). This distinction is a vital one, for (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)while risks of default can be addressed by a New Political Ecology(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %), the basic assumptions of which are by now generally accepted (indeed, they are already written into the International Rights of the Species), (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)there is absolutely nothing to counter this other immanent logic(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %), this speeding-up of everything(% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %), which plays double or nothing with nature. In the first case, the restoration of equilibrium to our ecological niche is(%%) still (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)possible(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %), the energies in play could still be rebalanced; in the second case, however, we are confronted by a development that is irretrievably out of balance. In the first case (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)ethical principles may be brought to bear(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %): a teleology that transcends the material Process involved - even if merely the goal of survival – may come into play; (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)in the second case(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %), however, (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight: lime&amp;#34; %)a process whose only goal is limitless proliferation will inevitably absorb all transcendence and devour all agents(%%) thereof. (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)A full-blown and planet-wide schizophrenia, therefore, now rules: even as all sorts of ecological measures are being taken, even as a strategy for (%%)the proper use of the world, for (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)an ideal interaction with the world, is being deployed, there is a simultaneous proliferation of enterprises of destruction, a total unleashing of the performance principle. And the very same forces often contribute to both trends.(%%) (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)Furthermore, though the end-point of the first tendency seems fairly clear - to wit, the saving of our species by means of ecological conviviality – we know absolutely nothing about the secret destination of the second. But surely (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)this acceleration(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %), this excentric motion, (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)must(%%) have an end, must (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)imply a destiny for the human species, a different symbolic relationship with the world that is much more complex(%%) and ambiguous (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime; mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)than a relationship of balance and interaction? This too would be a vital destination- but it would involve a total risk.(%%) (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)If such a destination has(%%) indeed (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)been chosen for us,(%%) it is obvious that (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)ecology&amp;#39;s rational deities will be powerless against the throwing of(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) technology and (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)energy into the struggle for an unpredictable goal(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %), in a sort of Great Game whose rules are unknown to us. (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)Even now we have no protection against the perverse effects of security, control and crime-prevention measures. We already know to what dangerous extremities we are led by prophylaxis in every sphere: social, medical, economic or political. In the name of the highest possible degree of security, an endemic terror may well be instituted that is in every way as dangerous as the epidemic threat of catastrophe. One thing is certain(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %): in view of the complexity of the initial conditions and the potential reversibility of all the effects, (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)we should entertain no illusions about the effectiveness(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %) (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)of any kind of rational intervention(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %). In the face of a process which so far surpasses the individual or collective will of the players, (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)we have no choice but to accept that any distinction between good and evil(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) (and by extension here any possibility of assessing the &amp;#39;right level&amp;#39; of technological development) (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)can have the slightest validity only within(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %) the tiny marginal sphere contributed by (% style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)our rational model. Inside these bounds, ethical reflection and practical determinations are feasible; beyond them(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt&amp;#34; %), at the level of the overall process which we have ourselves set in motion, but which from now on marches on independently of us with the ineluctability of a natural catastrophe, (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)there reigns(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) - for better or worse - (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)the inseparability of good and evil(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %), and hence the impossibility of mobilizing the one without the other. This is, properly speaking, the theorem of the accursed share. (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime; mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)There is no point(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) whatsoever (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;background:lime;mso-highlight:lime&amp;#34; %)in wondering whether things ought to be thus: they simply are thus, and to fail to acknowledge it is to fall utterly prey to illusion(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt&amp;#34; %). None of this invalidates whatever may be possible in the ethical, ecological or economic sphere of our life - but it does totally relativize the impact of such efforts upon the symbolic level, which is the level of destiny.

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; %)
 

==== We are confronted with the fate of energy, which is the fate of humanity. This deferred nuclear explosion will occur. We will be accelerated beyond all reason and control, and as the turbines of our power plants and as the wheels of society fall out of balance, the outcome will be catastrophic. We should no longer cling to rationality and restriction, producing continual Three Mile Islands or pragmatic alternatives, as these merely delay the catastrophe, but don&amp;#39;t prevent it. ====</headline></objectSummary><objectSummary><link rel="http://www.xwiki.org/rel/object" href="http://opencaselist.paperlessdebate.com/xwiki/rest/wikis/opencaselist/spaces/Texas-San%20Antonio/pages/nerison-stroud%20Aff/objects/Admin.EntryClass/6"/><link rel="http://www.xwiki.org/rel/properties" href="http://opencaselist.paperlessdebate.com/xwiki/rest/wikis/opencaselist/spaces/Texas-San%20Antonio/pages/nerison-stroud%20Aff/objects/Admin.EntryClass/6/properties"/><id>opencaselist:Texas-San Antonio.nerison-stroud Aff:d5ca5fda-d96e-44be-af01-d2cc9e7f957c</id><guid>d5ca5fda-d96e-44be-af01-d2cc9e7f957c</guid><pageId>opencaselist:Texas-San Antonio.nerison-stroud Aff</pageId><wiki>opencaselist</wiki><space>Texas-San Antonio</space><pageName>nerison-stroud Aff</pageName><className>Admin.EntryClass</className><number>6</number><headline>(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; %)&#xD;
